This paper deals with maintaining a maximal independent set in a dynamic graph, which is a problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents an algorithm that significantly improves the update time for uniformly sparse graphs, which is a property of the graph structure. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves complexity analysis, which suggests the sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
